I. Basic assumptions

1) CasperArmy Organization (also referred to as "CasperArmy") is the owner of the word and graphic mark "CasperArmy" (hereinafter referred to as the "logotype") and holds all copyrights and related rights to the logotype.

2. The logotype may only be used for promotional and informational purposes connected with CasperArmy.

3. The logotype may be used by:
- CasperArmy partners, on the basis of a declaration submitted and accepted by CasperArmy;
- Organisers of events, implementers of projects covered by the media patronage of CasperArmy;
- Projects incubated on the CasperArmy platform.
- Other entities that obtain permission from CasperArmy to use the logotype and sign a license agreement with CasperArmy.
Use of the logotype without the consent of CasperArmy will result in liability foreseen by the applicable provisions of law.

II. Procedure for applying for the use of the logotype

1. Potential CasperArmy partners, having become acquainted with the principles of cooperation with CasperArmy, submit a declaration, which requires CasperArmy's approval. The terms and conditions of cooperation and the declaration form are made available to the interested party individually via e-mail.

2. Organisers of events, project implementers apply for media patronage of CasperArmy. The application form and description of the procedure are available individually by e-mail. 

3. The use of the logotype by other entities is possible on the basis of previously obtained consent of CasperArmy and a license agreement concluded with CasperArmy. For this purpose, please contact Headquarters via email at: headquarter@casperarmy.org

4. The logotype is lent for free and available for download at https://github.com/casper-army/media-resources

III Terms & conditions of using the logotype 

1. The logotype must be used in a manner that prevents its distortion. In particular, it is prohibited to remove or add any verbal or graphic elements to the logotype. 

2. The size of the logotype is not reserved, but the proportions of its individual elements must be maintained.

3. The logotype cannot be a part of any other logotype.

4. The logotype may be placed next to other logotypes, provided that the space between the characters is at least 20 pixels.

5. The logotype placed on the websites and in electronic publications should be accompanied by a link to the website www.casperarmy.org

6. The entity intending to use the logotype is obliged to familiarize itself with the terms and conditions and accept them.

7. Downloading the logotype made available on the website https://github.com/casper-army/media-resources is tantamount to acceptance of the terms & conditions

IV. Final provisions

1. CasperArmy reserves the right to control entities in the scope of the use of the logotype and the right to take actions against entities acting contrary to the terms & conditions and violating commonly binding provisions of law. 

2. If the terms & conditions are violated, CasperArmy reserves the right to deny the use of the logotype. 

3. CasperArmy reserves the right to make changes to the terms & conditions. The amendments take effect from the moment they are published on the https://github.com/casper-army/media-resources website.
